Durban - The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal wants the party's national executive committee (NEC) to review its stance on support for former President Jacob Zuma when he appears in court on corruption charges. 
This comes as Zuma will be appearing at the Pietermaritzburg High court later this week.
Earlier this year, the NEC took a decision that no party structures should support Zuma when he appears in court. 

 







